  "area": "fft",
  "body_sections": [
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Computes the inverse of "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "rfftn"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "This function computes the inverse of the N-dimensional discrete\nFourier Transform for real input over any number of axes in an\nM-dimensional array by means of the Fast Fourier Transform (FFT).  In\nother words, "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "irfftn(rfftn(a), a.shape) == a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " to within numerical\naccuracy. (The "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a.shape"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is necessary like "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "len(a)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is for "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "irfft"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ",\nand for the same reason.)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The input should be ordered in the same way as is returned by "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "rfftn"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ",\ni.e. as for "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "irfft"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " for the final transformation axis, and as for "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "ifftn"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\nalong all the other axes."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Extended Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "Input array."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "array_like",
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "Input array."
                }
              ],
              "name": "a",
              "type": "field_list"
            },
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "Shape (length of each transformed axis) of the output\n("
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "s[0]"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " refers to axis 0, "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "s[1]"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " to axis 1, etc.). "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "s"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " is also the\nnumber of input points used along this axis, except for the last axis,\nwhere "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "s[-1]//2+1"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " points of the input are used.\nAlong any axis, if the shape indicated by "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "s"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " is smaller than that of\nthe input, the input is cropped.  If it is larger, the input is padded\nwith zeros."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "argument_inline": [],
                  "content_blocks": [],
                  "directive": "versionchanged",
                  "options": [],
                  "raw_source": ".. versionchanged:: 2.0\n\n    If it is ``-1``, the whole input is used (no padding/trimming).",
                  "supported": true,
                  "type": "directive_block",
                  "version": "2.0"
                },
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "If "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "s"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " is not given, the shape of the input along the axes\nspecified by axes is used. Except for the last axis which is taken to\nbe "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "2*(m-1)"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " where "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "m"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " is the length of the input along that axis."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "argument_inline": [],
                  "content_blocks": [],
                  "directive": "deprecated",
                  "options": [],
                  "raw_source": ".. deprecated:: 2.0\n\n    If `s` is not ``None``, `axes` must not be ``None`` either.",
                  "supported": true,
                  "type": "directive_block",
                  "version": "2.0"
                },
                {
                  "argument_inline": [],
                  "content_blocks": [],
                  "directive": "deprecated",
                  "options": [],
                  "raw_source": ".. deprecated:: 2.0\n\n    `s` must contain only ``int`` s, not ``None`` values. ``None``\n    values currently mean that the default value for ``n`` is used\n    in the corresponding 1-D transform, but this behaviour is\n    deprecated.",
                  "supported": true,
                  "type": "directive_block",
                  "version": "2.0"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "sequence of ints, optional",
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "Shape (length of each transformed axis) of the output\n("
                },
                {
                  "kind": "code",
                  "text": "s[0]"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": " refers to axis 0, "
                },
                {
                  "kind": "code",
                  "text": "s[1]"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": " to axis 1, etc.). "
                },
                {
                  "kind": "code",
                  "text": "s"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": " is also the\nnumber of input points used along this axis, except for the last axis,\nwhere "
                },
                {
                  "kind": "code",
                  "text": "s[-1]//2+1"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": " points of the input are used.\nAlong any axis, if the shape indicated by "
                },
                {
                  "kind": "code",
                  "text": "s"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": " is smaller than that of\nthe input, the input is cropped.  If it is larger, the input is padded\nwith zeros."
                }
              ],
              "name": "s",
              "type": "field_list"
            },
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "Axes over which to compute the inverse FFT. If not given, the last\n"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "len(s)"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " axes are used, or all axes if "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "s"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " is also not specified.\nRepeated indices in "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "axes"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " means that the inverse transform over that\naxis is performed multiple times."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "argument_inline": [],
                  "content_blocks": [],
                  "directive": "deprecated",
                  "options": [],
                  "raw_source": ".. deprecated:: 2.0\n\n    If `s` is specified, the corresponding `axes` to be transformed\n    must be explicitly specified too.",
                  "supported": true,
                  "type": "directive_block",
                  "version": "2.0"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "sequence of ints, optional",
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "Axes over which to compute the inverse FFT. If not given, the last\n"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "code",
                  "text": "len(s)"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": " axes are used, or all axes if "
                },
                {
                  "kind": "code",
                  "text": "s"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": " is also not specified.\nRepeated indices in "
                },
                {
                  "kind": "code",
                  "text": "axes"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": " means that the inverse transform over that\naxis is performed multiple times."
                }
              ],
              "name": "axes",
              "type": "field_list"
            },
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "Normalization mode (see "
                    },
                    {
                      "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.fft.html",
                      "href": "",
                      "kind": "link",
                      "target": "fft",
                      "text": "we.fft"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "). Default is \"backward\".\nIndicates which direction of the forward/backward pair of transforms\nis scaled and with what normalization factor."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "argument_inline": [],
                  "content_blocks": [],
                  "directive": "versionadded",
                  "options": [],
                  "raw_source": ".. versionadded:: 1.20.0\n\n    The \"backward\", \"forward\" values were added.",
                  "supported": true,
                  "type": "directive_block",
                  "version": "1.20.0"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "{\"backward\", \"ortho\", \"forward\"}, optional",
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "Normalization mode (see "
                },
                {
                  "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.fft.html",
                  "href": "",
                  "kind": "link",
                  "target": "fft",
                  "text": "we.fft"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "). Default is \"backward\".\nIndicates which direction of the forward/backward pair of transforms\nis scaled and with what normalization factor."
                }
              ],
              "name": "norm",
              "type": "field_list"
            },
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "If provided, the result will be placed in this array. It should be\nof the appropriate shape and dtype for the last transformation."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "argument_inline": [],
                  "content_blocks": [],
                  "directive": "versionadded",
